text: The Jejuy River (), a tributary of Paraguay River, is a river in Paraguay. Located in the northweastern part of that country, it flows eastwards discharging to Paraguay River north of Asunción. Aracaré was said to be from the Jejuy River. ==See also== *List of rivers of Paraguay ==References== Category:Rivers of Paraguay Category:Tributaries of the Paraguay River
title: Jejuy River
